<br>
It is soon going to be possible.  The enchanted mithril chain jointing was acknowledged as bugged and to be fixed by Verant.  Here is why this will be coming.<br>
<br>
Teir'Dal armor mirrors Koada'Dal armor in every way, as we are opposite sides of the same coin.  They too can make teir'dal chain for their casters to wear.  Their armor is nearly identical to our own, except when imbued it varies slightly.  A workaround was discovered to make the enchanted adamantite chain piece for the enchanted teir'dal plate using an ogre smith who also can make this piece.  A smith with 178 skill made an enchanted piece.  Apparently soon the patch is coming to fix this problem for both teir'dal and koada'dal I can't remember the name from Verant who was referenced.  <br>
<br>
What does this mean?  Enchanting armor raises the ac and provides stat bonuses.  Koada'dal mithril plate is half the weight of any other plate.  <br>
<br>
Who can wear it?  Elven Bards, Clerics, Warriors and Paladins.  This nudges this armor above Ro armor and slightly above Kylong.  Not bad for Preplanar.  The bracer AC is 10, wis and str bonus of 2 or 3 likely.  <br>
<br>
As soon as this is confirmed, I'll let you know.  Since elves are strength challenged, the light weight helps tremendously.  I'd expect many pieces of this armor to be excellent for clerics and paladins with the wisdom bonuses.<br>
<br>
On a side note, we have made some imbued elven chain already.  Any assistance obtaining swirling mist from Steamfont's mist elementals is appreciated.  If you obtain the ingredients of morning dew, swirling mist and essence of moonlight, I'll make the armor at cost for you.  I need to work up my skill.<br>
<br>
Thank you and good hunting. <p>Tearis Thex
