<br>
http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_velious_leathers.htm<br>
<br>
One must be a Grandmaster Tailor and a highly seasoned character to obtain the materials.  I would venture to say it is more challenging than being a cultural smith, though more profitable in the long run.<br>
<br>
Feir'Dal smiths make fine weapons which no other race of smiths can craft.  The only Feir'dal smith with this skill I know is Drinda.  These weapons are listed under Feir'dal smithing on the eqtraders site if interested in viewing their stats.  Koada'dal smithing only can produce falchions.<br>
<br>
The velious tailored armor has a unique sheen, fitting for a rogue stalking their prey.  <p>Tearis Thex
King of the Dal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub45.ezboard.com/utearis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tearis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://dalkingdom.freeservers.com/mith4.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#660000>(5/8/01 2:09:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Essence of Moonlight</span><hr size=1> Enchanted koada'dal plate is supposedly fixed with this patch (according to EQ Traders).  I'll find out later this week at the forge.<br>
<br>
If this is true, then about 1 in 8 attempts will succeed on average based on the attempts by folks in a similar skill range and stats to my own.  Koada'dal plate can be worn by Bards, Warriors, Clerics and Paladins.  It emanates light (can you say, "Target me while I'm medding please."), will have about a 10% increase in AC compared to normal koada'dal plate plus str/wis/MR stats (4/4/2 likely based on comparisons to Teir'dal enchanted plate stats).  The koada'dal plate is half the weight of normal plate and the ac is below average for cultural armors (bp ac is 20, versus 22 for kylong and crafted, though enchanted koada'dal plate may be 22, we'll see).<br>
<br>
An additional barrier comes into play for making this armor.  Like for imbued elven chain, mithril ore must be enchanted by a level 49+ enchanter.  Right now I'm having some trouble finding someone willing and able (lots of folks won't enchant for elf purists). <br>
<br>
So, if you know someone who can enchant mithril bricks (any race of enchanter can do this if they have the spell sold in Southern Felwithe), please let me know.  We are starting to accumulate some Moonlight Temper thanks to the efforts of many of you and our own folks, so all I need are some enchanted bricks and for Verant to have fixed this bug.<br>
<br>
Another bug said to have been fixed in today's patch is the chain boots recipe for cultural armor.  If this is true, I'll take these as well.<br>
<br>
Another step which saves time and hassle for me is if you can buy the large mithril bricks and have them enchanted ahead of time, then I can just smith.  <br>
<br>
Thank you. <p>Tearis Thex
